      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But expanding enforcement of the pay-to-play rule faces a key problem: The SEC has long delegated all of its enforcement authority to its staff, who appear to be all powerful when it comes to getting Wall Street off the hook and powerless to actually punish the industry for wrongdoing. The staff have routinely granted waivers even for standard-issue violations of the pay-to-play rule, as Gretchen Morgenson and Joshua Rosner reveal in their recent book ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 2,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "These Are The Plunderers: How Private Equity Runs ‚Äî and Wrecks ‚Äî America",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
